      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the priest shall make an atonement for him as concerning his sin; in a typical way, directing to the great sacrifice of Christ, which is the only real atonement and propitiation for sin: the Vulgate Latin, Syriac, and Arabic versions, render, \"the priest shall pray for him\": for the pardon of his sin: ",
        "children": []
